	&lt;li&gt;push out to 1.4&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13655622" author="kiranch" created="Sun, 12 May 2013 20:47:22 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;MultiValues are not stored for any metatags in the HTML and any metatag can have multiValued fields too. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When we use Tika for parsing with Nutch, we noticed that Tika does not store the multiValues for any html metatag. Tika only places one value in the DOM tree as reported in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NUTCH-1467&quot; title=&quot;nutch 1.5.1 not able to parse mutliValued metatags&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;NUTCH-1467&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;NUTCH-1467&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Does this patch allow Tika to have multiValues for any metatag or just OpenGraph metatags ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13656037" author="markus17" created="Mon, 13 May 2013 16:18:05 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Kiran - this patch works for any meta tag that has a `property` and a `content` attribute.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13656043" author="markus17" created="Mon, 13 May 2013 16:26:11 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;BTW, any reason why this is still not committed? The change is simple, has a test and all tests pass.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13656182" author="davemeikle" created="Mon, 13 May 2013 18:59:48 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Markus - looks like this one slipped through the net. Thanks for the patch, committed in r1481990.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13656913" author="markus17" created="Tue, 14 May 2013 10:02:50 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Dave. Marked as resolved.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
